cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning word representations and their syntactic and semantic regularities.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new objective function for learning word embeddings.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and learning word representations.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as word embeddings are also used in image captioning and other computer vision tasks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a new approach for learning word embeddings using Gaussian mixture models.
